Personal Productivity MCP Agent

A beginner-friendly AI-powered productivity assistant built with Python, Streamlit, OpenAI API, and the Model Context Protocol (MCP). The application demonstrates how an AI agent dynamically discovers and invokes tools from a local MCP server based on natural language requests, without requiring users to manually select tools.

Features
🤖 Chat-based AI assistant using OpenAI
🔌 Local MCP Server using FastMCP with stdio transport
📂 File management tools
Create, read, rename, move, delete files
Create folders
Save JSON data
📝 Notes management
Save persistent notes
Search notes by keyword
Retrieve current system date and time
🌦️ Live Weather
Uses Open-Meteo API (no API key required)
Current weather, temperature, humidity, wind speed, precipitation, and forecast
🔍 Live Web Search
Uses Tavily Search API for real-time news and information
💬 Intelligent tool selection
The AI automatically decides which MCP tool(s) to call based on the user's request
🔄 Multi-step task execution
Example:
Check weather
Search latest AI news
Summarize results
Save the report to a text file
📊 Streamlit Chat Interface
Chat history
Tool execution logs
MCP server status
Available tools, prompts, and resources displayed in the sidebar
